cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.DS

The paper proposes a deep-learning approach to learning the representation of states in partially observable tasks, which involves both supervised learning and reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with control optimization, which suggests the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves extensive experiments and data analysis, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
